            ]
        }
    ],
    [
        {
            "type": "title",
            "content": {
                "title_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "5.3 Deutsch-Jozsa algorithm"
                    }
                ],
                "level": 2
            },
            "bbox": [
                139,
                123,
                500,
                144
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Combining together the two preceding Sections leads to a generalization of the Deutsch algorithm, due to Deutsch and Jozsa. The circuit is:"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                137,
                152,
                857,
                188
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "content": {
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/906dea8c8a09c7a2cf99dd3f5564e77ccc6b4dd496c34f6b8c9b7afc553f0e55.jpg"
                },
                "content": "```mermaid\ngraph LR\n  A[\"|0⟩\"] -->|\"N\"| B[\"H⊗N\"]\n  C[\"|1⟩\"] --> D[\"H\"]\n  B --> E[\"Uf\"]\n  D --> E\n  E --> F[\"H⊗N\"]\n  F --> G[\"Output\"]\n```",
                "image_caption": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Fig. 5.3 Circuit for Deutsch-Jozsa algorithm f"
                    }
                ],
                "image_footnote": []
            },
            "sub_type": "flowchart",
            "bbox": [
                189,
                207,
                631,
                294
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "where the slash in the first line indicates N qubits in the first register. The input state is a "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "N + 1"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "qubit state "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "| 0 . . . 0 \\rangle | 1 \\rangle"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", with <sub>|</sub>0...0<sub>i</sub> = the state of N qubits all initialized to <sub>|</sub>0<sub>i</sub>. The "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "N + 1"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "qubit state emerging from the first battery of H gates is"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                137,
                345,
                858,
                410
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\frac {1}{\\sqrt {2 ^ {N}}} \\sum_ {x = 0} ^ {2 ^ {N} - 1} | x \\rangle \\frac {| 0 \\rangle - | 1 \\rangle}{\\sqrt {2}} \\tag {5.7}",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/30db267a773759d7d8105395e485dfbb5837ebd2c506b8175eb614b0524e60ce.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                401,
                410,
                855,
                457
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "which becomes, after applying "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "U _ { f } \\mathbf { \\hat { \\mathbf { \\Phi } } }"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                139,
                459,
                442,
                478
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\frac {1}{\\sqrt {2 ^ {N}}} \\sum_ {x = 0} ^ {2 ^ {N} - 1} | x \\rangle \\frac {| f (x) \\rangle - | 1 \\oplus f (x) \\rangle}{\\sqrt {2}} = \\frac {1}{\\sqrt {2 ^ {N}}} \\sum_ {x = 0} ^ {2 ^ {N} - 1} (- 1) ^ {f (x)} | x \\rangle \\frac {| 0 \\rangle - | 1 \\rangle}{\\sqrt {2}} \\tag {5.8}",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/b5853022095c21de5c2706cd7506307a150edd7e9471a2a092daf86e88c79f26.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                196,
                484,
                855,
                532
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Observe now that the action of "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "H ^ { \\otimes N }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "on "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "| x \\rangle = | x _ { 1 } \\rangle | x _ { 1 } \\rangle . . . | x _ { N } \\rangle"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ":"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                139,
                538,
                675,
                557
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "H ^ {\\otimes N} | x \\rangle = \\frac {1}{\\sqrt {2 ^ {N}}} (| 0 \\rangle + (- 1) ^ {x _ {1}} | 1 \\rangle) (| 0 \\rangle + (- 1) ^ {x _ {2}} | 1 \\rangle) \\dots (| 0 \\rangle + (- 1) ^ {x _ {N}} | 1 \\rangle) \\tag {5.9}",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/52bc1f15aee1fa423012bbdad7ef96f492d302d83beaf27720ea673634d9fa92.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                171,
                562,
                855,
                598
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "can also be written as"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                139,
                604,
                337,
                619
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "H ^ {\\otimes N} | x \\rangle = \\frac {1}{\\sqrt {2 ^ {N}}} \\sum_ {y = 0} ^ {2 ^ {N} - 1} (- 1) ^ {x \\cdot y} | y \\rangle \\tag {5.10}",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/ae572e0590dd07144d8a0e7445b7aef82c4219ecde656c43e694cc5afbcf7a7b.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                363,
                624,
                855,
                672
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "with the definition"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                139,
                678,
                305,
                694
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "x \\cdot y \\equiv x _ {1} y _ {1} \\oplus x _ {2} y _ {2} \\oplus \\dots \\oplus x _ {N} y _ {N} \\tag {5.11}",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/db3d27b1b9939dd178111ea866029c89b89c7144b4324f8678b431ad76b75e6c.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                357,
                695,
                853,
                714
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Then the state of the first N -qubit register before the measurement is"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                139,
                718,
                749,
                735
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\frac {1}{2 ^ {N}} \\sum_ {y = 0} ^ {2 ^ {N} - 1} \\left[ \\sum_ {x = 0} ^ {2 ^ {N} - 1} (- 1) ^ {f (x)} (- 1) ^ {x \\cdot y} \\right] | y \\rangle \\tag {5.12}",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/1f9a024f83d8ed0d2a9e6d3f802a90b3306ced1485867e43a9d6929d295fcf4b.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                349,
                739,
                855,
                796
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Thus the probability of finding "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "0 , 0 , . . . 0"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "in a measurement of the first register (N qubits) is"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                137,
                800,
                855,
                834
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "p (0, 0, \\dots 0) = \\left| \\frac {1}{2 ^ {N}} \\sum_ {x = 0} ^ {2 ^ {N} - 1} (- 1) ^ {f (x)} \\right| ^ {2} \\tag {5.13}",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/d25f26299080ac68c1e037ea39d1a3fcf7904b2cbed63856eac649048bbd5eef.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                357,
                834,
                855,
                891
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "page_number",
            "content": {
                "page_number_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "23"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                485,
                906,
                510,
                920
            ]
        }
    ],
    [
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "This probability is 1 if "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "f ( x )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is constant, and is 0 if "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "f ( x )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is balanced, i.e. with an equal number of values 1 and 0. Then by measuring the first register (N measurements) we can find whether "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "f"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is constant or not. The total number of operations grows linearly with "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "N"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", even considering the H gates in the circuit 5.3, and only one "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\mathrm { ^ { * } r u n } ^ { \\prime \\mathrm { * } }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "of "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "U _ { f }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is necessary."
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                137,
                125,
                853,
                210
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "By contrast, to obtain this information classically would require "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "2 ^ { N }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "evaluations of the function "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "f ,"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "growing exponentially with N."
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                137,
                211,
                853,
                245
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "page_number",
            "content": {
                "page_number_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "24"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                485,
                904,
                510,
                919
            ]
        }
    ]
]